			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2010</a> paper:</span><br><i>Domain-Specific Modelling Languages with Algebraic Graph Transformations on RDF</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/BenjaminBraatz.html">Benjamin Braatz</a>, <a href="../profile/ChristophBrandt.html">Christoph Brandt</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_6">10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_6</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagM">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> The paper is about defining/using a domain-specific modeling language on top of RDF data.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> Algebraic graph transformations are the key operational mechanism for processing/mapping RDF-based models.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3e.html"><span class="tagL">T3E: Ontologies</span></a><ul><li> RDF grounding places the approach in the ontology/semantic-web ecosystem.
</li></ul></li></ul>
